Mass. Gen. Laws ch. 185C, \u00a7 16A.proposition: 3. This court has jurisdiction over this matter pursuant to Mass. Gen. Laws ch. 185C, § 16A which grants jurisdiction to district courts over landlord-tenant disputes, as well as under applicable principles of common law.

Mass. Gen. Laws ch. 186 \u00a7 14.proposition: 10. Plaintiff alleges a single cause of action for breach of the covenant of quiet enjoyment, as codified under Mass. Gen. Laws ch. 186 § 14, which guarantees tenants the right to hot water in their leased premises.
